1
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:29,240
On December 8, 1941,

2
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:31,960
Japan launched an invasion of Malaya,

3
00:01:32,600 --> 00:01:35,120
which subsequently fell completely.

4
00:01:36,080 --> 00:01:36,610
Mingwei.

5
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:37,240
Slow down.

6
00:01:37,360 --> 00:01:37,720
Over there.

7
00:01:37,720 --> 00:01:38,250
Mingwei.

8
00:01:39,080 --> 00:01:39,610
Mingwei.

9
00:01:39,759 --> 00:01:40,160
Hurry.

10
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:41,440
Bandage him up.

11
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:45,660
Mr. Qin.

12
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:47,560
I wonder

13
00:01:48,479 --> 00:01:49,920
how Jiadong is doing now.

14
00:01:50,720 --> 00:01:51,979
According to the time.

15
00:01:52,240 --> 00:01:54,080
They arrived last night

16
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,800
at the Xiamen freight terminal.

17
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:57,060
If nothing goes wrong,

18
00:01:57,640 --> 00:01:58,560
he is currently heading

19
00:01:58,560 --> 00:01:59,759
to the city of Xiamen.

20
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:20,960
Jiadong.

21
00:02:27,120 --> 00:02:27,650
Wangshu.

22
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:29,890
Wangshu, what's wrong?

23
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:31,450
Sister-in-law.

24
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:32,560
I had a nightmare.

25
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:34,760
What did you dream about?

26
00:02:34,760 --> 00:02:36,020
I dreamed that Jiadong

27
00:02:36,760 --> 00:02:38,240
was on a boat hit by a bomb,

28
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:39,940
and then fell into the sea.

29
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,060
That won't happen.

30
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:45,320
Dreams are the opposite of reality.

31
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:47,760
Jiadong will surely come back safely.

32
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:49,850
Don't overthink it.

33
00:02:52,200 --> 00:02:53,130
Sister-in-law.

34
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:55,290
How long has Jiadong been gone?

35
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:57,000
Almost...

36
00:02:58,200 --> 00:02:59,079
Almost a month.

37
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:01,570
He should have been back by now.

38
00:03:02,920 --> 00:03:03,960
But why

39
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,690
haven't we heard anything yet?

40
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:06,520
Maybe

41
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:07,960
he got delayed

42
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:09,020
by something else.

43
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:10,920
I heard Malaya

44
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:12,680
has been occupied by the Japanese.

45
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:13,340
Do you think

46
00:03:13,480 --> 00:03:14,960
he will be alright?

47
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:17,079
Don't worry.

48
00:03:17,560 --> 00:03:19,960
Jiadong will definitely come back safely.

49
00:03:22,040 --> 00:03:22,760
Don't cry.

50
00:03:23,960 --> 00:03:26,090
Be careful with the baby in your belly.

51
00:03:30,280 --> 00:03:31,010
Brother Jiu,

52
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:32,900
we caught a big fish this time.

53
00:03:34,079 --> 00:03:35,140
What did you catch?

54
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:36,329
Brother Jiu,

55
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:37,079
this kid

56
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:38,200
brought such a big bag.

57
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:38,920
It must be full of

58
00:03:38,920 --> 00:03:40,440
valuable things for his escape.

59
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:41,170
Brother Jiu,

60
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:42,160
we're rich!

61
00:03:42,640 --> 00:03:44,640
Open it and see what treasures are inside.

62
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:45,640
Don't touch them!

63
00:03:47,640 --> 00:03:48,240
Brothers,

64
00:03:48,720 --> 00:03:50,720
I am a courier for the Qiaopi office.

65
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:52,520
The things in these boxes

66
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:53,400
are Qiaopi.

67
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:55,160
Please don't touch them.

68
00:03:57,079 --> 00:03:58,480
You've got a lot of nerve,

69
00:03:59,160 --> 00:04:00,600
yelling at us like that.

70
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:02,920
Do you know where you are?

71
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:06,500
I was just about to ask,

72
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:07,920
where is this place?

73
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:10,760
And who might you three be?

74
00:04:11,440 --> 00:04:12,240
Tell him.

75
00:04:13,600 --> 00:04:14,080
Boy,

76
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:15,360
listen up.

77
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:17,120
This is Heilongkou,

78
00:04:17,279 --> 00:04:18,320
Jiu's territory.

79
00:04:19,640 --> 00:04:20,360
Jiu?

80
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,640
You mean the pirate, Jiu?

81
00:04:24,240 --> 00:04:25,900
How dare you call him a pirate!

82
00:04:26,360 --> 00:04:27,320
I'll kill you!

83
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:28,000
Wait.

84
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:41,440
What did you just say?

85
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:43,880
You're a letter carrier?

86
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:45,360
Yes.

87
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:45,920
Yes.

88
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:49,200
You know no one

89
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:50,640
would rob a letter carrier,

90
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:52,370
so you pretend to be one, right?

91
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:53,520
Boy,

92
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:55,480
I've seen plenty of letter carriers.

93
00:04:55,480 --> 00:04:56,440
How dare you lie to me!

94
00:04:56,440 --> 00:04:57,040
Bro.

95
00:04:57,440 --> 00:04:58,400
I'm not lying to you.

96
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:00,080
I'm a letter carrier from Malaya,

97
00:05:00,080 --> 00:05:01,480
delivering letters to Quanzhou.

98
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:02,540
Please, you three,

99
00:05:02,640 --> 00:05:03,300
let me pass.

100
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:05,140
Open it.

101
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:05,770
Okay.

102
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:18,120
What else?

103
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:22,340
Nothing else, bro.

104
00:05:24,440 --> 00:05:25,440
A letter carrier.

105
00:05:26,280 --> 00:05:28,280
How come there are no letters at all?

106
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:31,280
These medicines are my letters from overseas.

107
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:34,240
How dare you lie to me?

108
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:38,560
Hello, brother.

109
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:39,120
I want to ask,

110
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:39,520
have you seen

111
00:05:39,520 --> 00:05:40,560
a young man?

112
00:05:40,560 --> 00:05:41,620
I haven't seen him.

113
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:44,200
Hello.

114
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:45,080
I want to ask,

115
00:05:45,080 --> 00:05:46,240
have you seen a courier

116
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:47,200
named Chen Jiadong?

117
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:48,130
About this tall.

118
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:51,200
Sir,

119
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:52,320
I'd like to ask

120
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:52,840
if you've seen

121
00:05:52,840 --> 00:05:54,500
a courier named Chen Jiadong.

122
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:55,560
He's about this tall,

123
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:56,840
with a high nose bridge.

124
00:05:56,840 --> 00:05:57,840
I don't know, miss.

125
00:05:57,840 --> 00:05:58,960
You should ask the crew.

126
00:05:58,960 --> 00:05:59,890
They might know.

127
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:06,280
Ma'am,

128
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:08,560
are there any more boats coming?

129
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:09,280
No more.

130
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:11,530
I already asked.

131
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:13,570
This is the last one.

132
00:06:29,440 --> 00:06:30,160
Wangshu,

133
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:31,680
let's go home.

134
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:33,760
You need to rest now.

135
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:36,050
Be careful not to harm the baby.

136
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:37,000
Yes, Wangshu.

137
00:06:38,480 --> 00:06:39,200
No.

138
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:41,560
Jiadong will be fine.

139
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:44,159
He promised me

140
00:06:44,159 --> 00:06:45,640
he would return safely.

141
00:06:46,880 --> 00:06:47,760
He will be with me

142
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:49,360
to see the birth of our child.

143
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:50,960
He will.

144
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:52,530
Jiadong,

145
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:54,360
you promised me.

146
00:06:55,440 --> 00:06:57,240
We prayed under the sacred tree.

147
00:06:57,520 --> 00:06:59,180
You can't break your promise.

148
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:06,170
Brother Jiu.

149
00:07:06,280 --> 00:07:07,320
I've counted it all.

150
00:07:07,320 --> 00:07:08,920
123 silver dollars in total,

151
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:10,720
and a money order.

152
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:11,660
Here, look.

153
00:07:17,280 --> 00:07:18,610
So many silver dollars.

154
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:19,210
Brother,

155
00:07:19,840 --> 00:07:20,920
we hit the jackpot.

156
00:07:21,320 --> 00:07:22,440
We're rich.

157
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:28,080
What is this stuff?

158
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:29,280
Just bottles and jars.

159
00:07:29,280 --> 00:07:30,410
They're worthless.

160
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:32,580
Don't throw them. Give them to me.

161
00:07:40,159 --> 00:07:40,600
Ah San,

162
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:42,930
you've had some schooling.

163
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:43,680
Take a look.

164
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:44,610
What does it say?

165
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:50,440
Brother Jiu.

166
00:07:50,440 --> 00:07:51,960
It's all in a foreign language.

167
00:07:51,960 --> 00:07:53,220
I can't read it either.

168
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:55,290
How would I know?

169
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:57,810
This looks like Western medicine.

170
00:07:58,520 --> 00:07:59,780
What kind of medicine?

171
00:08:01,360 --> 00:08:02,360
It's penicillin.

172
00:08:11,280 --> 00:08:11,840
Wangshu.

173
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:13,560
Go get some rest.

174
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:16,890
Sister-in-law, I'm not tired.

175
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,930
The Japanese bombing a few days ago

176
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:20,880
forced our remittance bureau

177
00:08:20,880 --> 00:08:22,240
to close for so long.

178
00:08:23,320 --> 00:08:25,580
Now we need to reopen as soon as possible.

179
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:28,240
Look at all these backlogged remittances.

180
00:08:28,240 --> 00:08:29,920
We need to sort them out as quickly as possible

181
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:30,600
and deliver them early

182
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:32,059
to the recipients' homes.

183
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:34,360
You must know they are just like us,

184
00:08:35,280 --> 00:08:37,559
waiting for remittances from their loved ones.

185
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:38,559
I know.

186
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:40,880
I'll handle all of this.

187
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,330
You go get some rest.

188
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:44,680
You don't even know how to

189
00:08:44,680 --> 00:08:46,240
sort these remittances yet.

190
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:46,570
Come.

191
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:47,890
Let me teach you.

192
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:49,900
Right now, in all of Quanzhou,

193
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:50,800
only our

194
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:52,240
Lin family's Wansheng Bureau

195
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:53,160
has reopened.

196
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:55,800
With so many backlogged remittances,

197
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:58,260
we have to find a way to send them out quickly.

198
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:02,400
If only Jiadong were here.

199
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,860
He is familiar with every road

200
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:08,160
and every family of overseas Chinese here.

201
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:09,530
Starting tomorrow,

202
00:09:09,680 --> 00:09:11,210
I will deliver the letters.

203
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:12,280
Uncle Lin,

204
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:13,520
your legs can't walk

205
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:14,480
such a long way.

206
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:16,760
They are much better now.

207
00:09:17,920 --> 00:09:19,580
I grew up delivering letters.

208
00:09:19,680 --> 00:09:21,680
This work is nothing to me.

209
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:25,200
Jiadong,

210
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:27,720
where exactly are you now?

211
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:31,520
Listen to me.

212
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:33,730
Answer me when I ask you a question.

213
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:35,040
If you dare to lie to me again,

214
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:36,040
I will chop you up.

215
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:37,720
Okay, bro, tell me.

216
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:38,460
Tell me,

217
00:09:39,160 --> 00:09:40,290
who exactly are you?

218
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:42,560
I'm a letter deliverer

219
00:09:42,560 --> 00:09:44,000
for Wansheng Post Office in Malaya.

220
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,240
My name is Chen Jiadong.

221
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:47,240
Where did the silver coins and money orders come from?

222
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:49,880
Someone entrusted them to me.

223
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:52,420
Who are they for and what are they for?

224
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:54,720
I can't tell you.

225
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:57,180
Then let me ask you,

226
00:09:58,160 --> 00:09:59,960
where did those Western medicines come from?

227
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:01,290
I can't tell you either.

228
00:10:03,160 --> 00:10:05,200
You can't make up any more lies, can you?

229
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:06,730
Can't make them up anymore.

230
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:08,880
Do you think I don't know?

231
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:12,050
These Western medicines are called penicillin.

232
00:10:12,080 --> 00:10:14,320
They are the most precious life-saving medicines right now.

233
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:15,160
In the Xiamen black market,

234
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:16,200
they are sold at sky-high prices.

235
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:17,600
Do you think I don't know?

236
00:10:17,920 --> 00:10:18,380
Really?

237
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:19,280
Really.

238
00:10:19,880 --> 00:10:20,960
You black-hearted,

239
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:22,020
stinky merchants,

240
00:10:22,040 --> 00:10:23,280
only know how to make money.

241
00:10:23,280 --> 00:10:23,800
You never care about

242
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:25,320
the lives of us poor people.

243
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:27,520
Bro, I'm not a black-hearted merchant.

244
00:10:29,520 --> 00:10:29,980
Tell me.

245
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:33,040
Which firm are these goods sent to?

246
00:10:33,440 --> 00:10:34,560
Where is the address?

247
00:10:34,560 --> 00:10:36,220
What is the shop owner's name?

248
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:38,800
Bro, why are you asking this?

249
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:40,820
I'll deliver these goods for you.

250
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:43,440
After I deliver the goods and get the money,

251
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:44,840
I'll spare your dog life.

252
00:10:48,480 --> 00:10:49,810
I can't tell you either.

253
00:10:51,160 --> 00:10:52,160
You won't tell me?

254
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:55,090
It seems you want money over your life.

255
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:56,880
I'll help you with that.

256
00:10:56,880 --> 00:10:58,740
This is anti-Japanese medicine.

257
00:10:59,040 --> 00:10:59,970
What did you say?

258
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:01,560
These are Western medicines

259
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:03,160
obtained by overseas Chinese in Malaya with great difficulty.

260
00:11:03,160 --> 00:11:04,640
They are life-saving medicines for

261
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:05,280
the anti-Japanese soldiers on the front line.
